{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783115705,"nonce":"S/rJdbwOWS2ZvO23/ArsSd7HNOA=","kind":"plan","title":"Config + favorites — implementation plan"},{"type":9,"timestamp":1783115705,"nonce":"Jq4/Tr4/qSFegCEafgtRodiPFcM=","label":"area:design"},{"type":11,"timestamp":1783115705,"nonce":"hTZ9dcbT2i33jsOwd52OdhlHPlY=","actor":"Trevor Vaughan","actor_kind":"human","source_path":"","trigger":"create"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1783115705,"nonce":"I8gyiwIWd7FW3DVZjR6uOGU4MAI=","body":"# Config + Favorites Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Add kref's first configuration system — a two-layer config (user YAML file + shared `kind:config` entry) with versioned migrations, a trust boundary, and a favorites/alias facility resolvable anywhere an id is.\n\n**Architecture:** A new `internal/config` package owns the schema, load pipeline, lint, and migrations (yaml.v3, no viper). `store.Open` loads the effective config; `Store.Resolve` folds favorite-name lookup ahead of hex-prefix resolution (namespaces kept disjoint by a non-hex-char rule, so no precedence ambiguity). New cobra commands `kref config` and `kref fav` (alias `alt`) live in `cmd/kref`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, cobra, `gopkg.in/yaml.v3` (already a direct dep), ginkgo/gomega (project test convention), Venom (e2e).\n\n**Spec:** kref entry `fca1e73ab8c5` (`kref show fca1e73ab8c5`). Re-read it before starting.\n\n**Conventions to honor:**\n- Run tests with `task test` (wires `KREF_BETTERLEAKS`); a bare `go test ./...` misses scan/e2e wiring. Rebuild the smoke binary with `go build -o /workspace/kref ./cmd/kref` when exercising the CLI by hand (see the repo memory on stale `./bin/kref`).\n- Tests that shell to git must null the caller's git config: set `GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL=/dev/null GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM=/dev/null` and kref-specific `GIT_AUTHOR_*`/`GIT_COMMITTER_*`.\n- Commit at every task boundary. Branch is `feat/edited-timestamp`'s successor — create `feat/config-favorites` first (Task 0).\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n**New files:**\n- `internal/config/config.go` — `Config` struct, compiled-in defaults, `CurrentVersion`, `Merge`, effective-value accessors.\n- `internal/config/lint.go` — `Validate(*Config) error` (schema + semantic), favorite-name rule `ValidFavoriteName`.\n- `internal/config/io.go` — user-file path (XDG), read/parse, atomic write with `.bck`, template emission.\n- `internal/config/migrate.go` — `CurrentVersion`, ordered migration chain over `*yaml.Node`, `Migrate`.\n- `internal/config/config_suite_test.go` — ginkgo bootstrap for the package.\n- `internal/config/config_test.go`, `lint_test.go`, `migrate_test.go` — unit specs.\n- `cmd/kref/config.go` — `newConfigCmd` (`init`/`edit`/`check`/`migrate` + bare effective view).\n- `cmd/kref/fav.go` — `newFavCmd` (`add`/`rm`/`ls`, alias `alt`).\n- `test/e2e/config-favorites.venom.yml` — e2e suite (match the existing e2e dir/naming).\n\n**Modified files:**\n- `internal/store/store.go` — load config in `Open`; `Favorites()` accessor; fold favorites into `Resolve`.\n- `internal/store/config.go` (new, store-side) — discover the `kind:config` entry, read+trust-filter it, produce the project layer; write path for `--shared`.\n- `internal/render/render.go` — `ShowHeader` gains a `Favorites` row.\n- `cmd/kref/main.go` — register `newConfigCmd` (setup group) and `newFavCmd` (core group).\n- `cmd/kref/commands.go` — `newShowCmd` passes reverse-looked-up favorite names into `ShowHeader`.\n- `cmd/kref/agentsmd.go`, `README.md` — document config + favorites.\n\n**Package boundary:** `internal/config` is store-agnostic — it parses/validates/migrates YAML bytes and merges layers. The store-side `internal/store/config.go` supplies the project-entry *bytes* (discovery + trust filtering happens there, because trust filtering needs the user file's `trusted_keys`, which `internal/config` produces). This keeps `internal/config` free of git-bug imports and unit-testable on plain bytes.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Config core (schema, load, lint)\n\n### Task 0: Branch\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Create the feature branch**\n\nRun:\n```bash\ncd /workspace \u0026\u0026 git checkout -b feat/config-favorites\n```\nExpected: `Switched to a new branch 'feat/config-favorites'`\n\n### Task 1: Config struct + defaults + ginkgo suite\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/config/config.go`\n- Create: `internal/config/config_suite_test.go`\n- Create: `internal/config/config_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the ginkgo suite bootstrap**\n\n`internal/config/config_suite_test.go`:\n```go\npackage config_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n)\n\nfunc TestConfig(t *testing.T) {\n\tRegisterFailHandler(Fail)\n\tRunSpecs(t, \"Config Suite\")\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing test for defaults + Merge**\n\n`internal/config/config_test.go`:\n```go\npackage config_test\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/config\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Config\", func() {\n\tIt(\"defaults warn_unscanned to true and trusted_keys to the safe set\", func() {\n\t\tc := config.Default()\n\t\tExpect(c.WarnUnscanned).To(BeTrue())\n\t\tExpect(c.TrustedKeys).To(ConsistOf(\"favorites\", \"warn_unscanned\"))\n\t\tExpect(c.Version).To(Equal(config.CurrentVersion))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"merges user over project per-key and unions favorites with user winning\", func() {\n\t\tproject := \u0026config.Config{WarnUnscanned: false, Favorites: map[string]string{\"todo\": \"aaa\", \"spec\": \"bbb\"}}\n\t\tuser := \u0026config.Config{Favorites: map[string]string{\"todo\": \" zzz \"[1:4]}} // \"zzz\"\n\t\teff := config.Merge(project, user)\n\t\tExpect(eff.Favorites).To(HaveKeyWithValue(\"todo\", \"zzz\")) // user wins\n\t\tExpect(eff.Favorites).To(HaveKeyWithValue(\"spec\", \"bbb\")) // project survives\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/config/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: config.Default` / `config.Config` / `config.Merge`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Implement the struct, defaults, and Merge**\n\n`internal/config/config.go`:\n```go\n// Package config owns kref's user + project configuration: schema, defaults,\n// layered merge, validation, and versioned migration. It operates on YAML\n// bytes and plain structs only (no git-bug imports); the store supplies the\n// project-entry bytes and applies the trust filter.\npackage config\n\n// CurrentVersion is the config schema version this binary writes. Bump it in\n// migrate.go alongside a new migration step.\nconst CurrentVersion = 1\n\n// Config is the effective, merged configuration. Zero values are meaningful\n// only after Default()/Merge(): callers must not construct a bare Config for\n// runtime use.\ntype Config struct {\n\tVersion       int               `yaml:\"version\"`\n\tWarnUnscanned bool              `yaml:\"warn_unscanned\"`\n\tFavorites     map[string]string `yaml:\"favorites,omitempty\"`\n\t// TrustedKeys is honored ONLY from the user file. It is the root of trust:\n\t// it gates which keys a config entry may contribute. Never read it from an\n\t// entry (see internal/store/config.go).\n\tTrustedKeys []string `yaml:\"trusted_keys,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// Default returns the compiled-in defaults. A sparse/absent file resolves to\n// these, so missing keys never break a load.\nfunc Default() *Config {\n\treturn \u0026Config{\n\t\tVersion:       CurrentVersion,\n\t\tWarnUnscanned: true,\n\t\tFavorites:     map[string]string{},\n\t\tTrustedKeys:   []string{\"favorites\", \"warn_unscanned\"},\n\t}\n}\n\n// Merge layers user over project per key. Favorites union by name with the user\n// value winning on collision. TrustedKeys is taken from user only (root of\n// trust). project or user may be nil.\nfunc Merge(project, user *Config) *Config {\n\tout := Default()\n\tapply := func(c *Config, trusted bool) {\n\t\tif c == nil {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t\tout.WarnUnscanned = c.WarnUnscanned\n\t\tfor k, v := range c.Favorites {\n\t\t\tout.Favorites[k] = v\n\t\t}\n\t\tif trusted \u0026\u0026 len(c.TrustedKeys) \u003e 0 {\n\t\t\tout.TrustedKeys = append([]string(nil), c.TrustedKeys...)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tapply(project, false)\n\tapply(user, true) // user last =\u003e user wins; trusted =\u003e may set TrustedKeys\n\tout.Version = CurrentVersion\n\treturn out\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/config/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: PASS (2 specs).\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace \u0026\u0026 git add internal/config/config.go internal/config/config_suite_test.go internal/config/config_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(config): add config schema, defaults, and layered merge\"\n```\n\n### Task 2: Favorite-name rule + lint\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/config/lint.go`\n- Create: `internal/config/lint_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n`internal/config/lint_test.go`:\n```go\npackage config_test\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/config\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"ValidFavoriteName\", func() {\n\tDescribeTable(\"accepts names disjoint from hex ids\",\n\t\tfunc(name string, ok bool) {\n\t\t\terr := config.ValidFavoriteName(name)\n\t\t\tif ok {\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tEntry(\"todo\", \"todo\", true),\n\t\tEntry(\"roadmap\", \"roadmap\", true),\n\t\tEntry(\"spec-1\", \"spec-1\", true),\n\t\tEntry(\"bare hex beef\", \"beef\", false),\n\t\tEntry(\"bare hex 1234\", \"1234\", false),\n\t\tEntry(\"deadbeef\", \"deadbeef\", false),\n\t\tEntry(\"reserved kref.conf\", \"kref.conf\", false),\n\t\tEntry(\"leading dash\", \"-x\", false),\n\t\tEntry(\"whitespace\", \"a b\", false),\n\t\tEntry(\"empty\", \"\", false),\n\t)\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Validate\", func() {\n\tIt(\"rejects an unknown key\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(config.Validate(\u0026config.Config{Version: 1, Unknown: true})).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n\tIt(\"rejects a favorite whose name violates the rule\", func() {\n\t\tc := config.Default()\n\t\tc.Favorites = map[string]string{\"beef\": \"aaa\"}\n\t\tExpect(config.Validate(c)).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n\tIt(\"accepts the defaults\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(config.Validate(config.Default())).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\nNote: `config.Config` has no `Unknown` field — unknown-key rejection is enforced at *parse* time via `yaml.Node` decoding with `KnownFields(true)` (Task 3), not on the struct. Replace the \"rejects an unknown key\" spec with the parse-level test in Task 3 and delete it here.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/config/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: config.ValidFavoriteName` / `config.Validate`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement lint + the name rule**\n\n`internal/config/lint.go`:\n```go\npackage config\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"regexp\"\n\t\"strings\"\n)\n\n// reservedFavoriteNames may not be user-assigned. kref.conf is the project\n// config entry's own alias.\nvar reservedFavoriteNames = map[string]bool{\"kref.conf\": true}\n\n// hexOnly matches a string made entirely of lowercase hex digits — exactly the\n// shape of an id prefix. A favorite name must NOT match this, so favorite and\n// id namespaces are disjoint and resolution needs no precedence rule.\nvar hexOnly = regexp.MustCompile(`^[0-9a-f]+$`)\n\n// ValidFavoriteName enforces the disjoint-namespace + hygiene rules.\nfunc ValidFavoriteName(name string) error {\n\tswitch {\n\tcase name == \"\":\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"favorite name is empty\")\n\tcase reservedFavoriteNames[name]:\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"favorite name %q is reserved\", name)\n\tcase strings.HasPrefix(name, \"-\"):\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"favorite name %q may not start with '-'\", name)\n\tcase strings.ContainsAny(name, \" \\t\\n\\r\"):\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"favorite name %q may not contain whitespace\", name)\n\tcase hexOnly.MatchString(name):\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"favorite name %q is a valid hex id-prefix and would shadow an id; use a name containing a non-hex character\", name)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// Validate is the linter: schema + semantic checks shared by every write path\n// and exposed read-only by `kref config check`.\nfunc Validate(c *Config) error {\n\tif c.Version \u003c= 0 {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"config: missing or invalid version\")\n\t}\n\tfor name := range c.Favorites {\n\t\tif err := ValidFavoriteName(name); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"config: favorites: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tknown := map[string]bool{\"favorites\": true, \"warn_unscanned\": true}\n\tfor _, k := range c.TrustedKeys {\n\t\tif !known[k] {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"config: trusted_keys names unknown key %q\", k)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\nDelete the `config.Config{... Unknown: true}` spec from `lint_test.go` (unknown-key rejection is parse-time; see Task 3).\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/config/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace \u0026\u0026 git add internal/config/lint.go internal/config/lint_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(config): add lint and the disjoint favorite-name rule\"\n```\n\n### Task 3: Parse user file (strict) + XDG path + write with .bck\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/config/io.go`\n- Create: `internal/config/io_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n`internal/config/io_test.go`:\n```go\npackage config_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/config\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Parse\", func() {\n\tIt(\"rejects an unknown key (strict decode)\", func() {\n\t\t_, err := config.Parse([]byte(\"version: 1\\nbogus: true\\n\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n\tIt(\"fills defaults for absent keys\", func() {\n\t\tc, err := config.Parse([]byte(\"version: 1\\n\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(c.WarnUnscanned).To(BeTrue()) // default applied\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"WriteFile\", func() {\n\tIt(\"backs up an existing file to .bck before writing\", func() {\n\t\tdir := GinkgoT().TempDir()\n\t\tp := filepath.Join(dir, \"config.yaml\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(p, []byte(\"version: 1\\nwarn_unscanned: true\\n\"), 0o600)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(config.WriteFile(p, config.Default())).To(Succeed())\n\t\t_, err := os.Stat(p + \".bck\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"UserPath\", func() {\n\tIt(\"honors XDG_CONFIG_HOME\", func() {\n\t\tget := func(k string) string {\n\t\t\tif k == \"XDG_CONFIG_HOME\" {\n\t\t\t\treturn \"/xdg\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn \"\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(config.UserPath(get)).To(Equal(\"/xdg/kref/config.yaml\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/config/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: config.Parse/WriteFile/UserPath`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement io.go**\n\n`internal/config/io.go`:\n```go\npackage config\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\n\t\"gopkg.in/yaml.v3\"\n)\n\n// UserPath returns $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/kref/config.yaml (or $HOME/.config/... ).\n// getenv is injected for testability (pass os.Getenv in production).\nfunc UserPath(getenv func(string) string) (string, error) {\n\tbase := getenv(\"XDG_CONFIG_HOME\")\n\tif base == \"\" {\n\t\thome := getenv(\"HOME\")\n\t\tif home == \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"cannot resolve config path: neither XDG_CONFIG_HOME nor HOME is set\")\n\t\t}\n\t\tbase = filepath.Join(home, \".config\")\n\t}\n\treturn filepath.Join(base, \"kref\", \"config.yaml\"), nil\n}\n\n// Parse decodes config bytes with unknown keys rejected, then overlays the\n// parsed values onto Default() so absent keys take their default.\nfunc Parse(b []byte) (*Config, error) {\n\tvar node yaml.Node\n\tif err := yaml.Unmarshal(b, \u0026node); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"config: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tc := Default()\n\tdec := yaml.NewDecoder(nil) // placeholder; replaced below\n\t_ = dec\n\t// Strict decode: KnownFields(true) rejects bogus keys.\n\tif len(node.Content) \u003e 0 {\n\t\td := yaml.NewDecoder(bytesReader(b))\n\t\td.KnownFields(true)\n\t\toverlay := \u0026Config{}\n\t\tif err := d.Decode(overlay); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"config: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tmergeOverlay(c, overlay, b)\n\t}\n\treturn c, nil\n}\n```\n\nNote to implementer: `yaml.NewDecoder` needs an `io.Reader`; add a small `bytesReader(b []byte) io.Reader { return bytes.NewReader(b) }` helper (import `bytes`, `io`), and delete the placeholder `dec` lines. `mergeOverlay(dst, overlay, raw)` must apply only the keys actually present in `raw` — decode `raw` into a `map[string]yaml.Node` to learn which top-level keys are set, then copy those fields from `overlay` onto `dst`. Keep it explicit for the four known keys.\n\n```go\n// WriteFile writes c to path atomically, backing up any existing file to\n// path+\".bck\" first. The output is the commented template with c's values.\nfunc WriteFile(path string, c *Config) error {\n\tif existing, err := os.ReadFile(path); err == nil {\n\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(path+\".bck\", existing, 0o600); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"config: backup: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tout, err := Template(c)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(path), 0o700); err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\ttmp := path + \".tmp\"\n\tif err := os.WriteFile(tmp, out, 0o600); err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\treturn os.Rename(tmp, path)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Implement Template (commented, canonical)**\n\nAdd to `internal/config/io.go`:\n```go\n// Template renders the canonical commented config with c's values. It is the\n// single source of truth for the file's shape and documentation (shipped in\n// the binary, like agents_md/completion). Migration regenerates comments from\n// here rather than preserving user comments (the .bck retains the original).\nfunc Template(c *Config) ([]byte, error) {\n\tfavs, err := yaml.Marshal(map[string]map[string]string{\"favorites\": c.Favorites})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\t_ = favs // favorites block appended only when non-empty; see below\n\tvar b []byte\n\tb = append(b, []byte(fmt.Sprintf(\"# kref configuration. Managed by `kref config`.\\nversion: %d\\n\\n\", c.Version))...)\n\tb = append(b, []byte(\"# Silence the \\\"stored UNSCANNED\\\" warning when betterleaks is absent.\\n\")...)\n\tb = append(b, []byte(fmt.Sprintf(\"warn_unscanned: %t\\n\\n\", c.WarnUnscanned))...)\n\tb = append(b, []byte(\"# Keys a kref config ENTRY (project config, teammate-editable) may set.\\n\"+\n\t\t\"# Entries are NOT fully trusted. 'scanners' is deliberately omitted: it\\n\"+\n\t\t\"# names executables that run on ingest, and a synced entry must not choose\\n\"+\n\t\t\"# what runs on your machine. This key is honored ONLY from this file.\\n\")...)\n\ttk, err := yaml.Marshal(map[string][]string{\"trusted_keys\": c.TrustedKeys})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\tb = append(b, tk...)\n\tif len(c.Favorites) \u003e 0 {\n\t\tb = append(b, '\\n')\n\t\tfb, err := yaml.Marshal(map[string]map[string]string{\"favorites\": c.Favorites})\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tb = append(b, fb...)\n\t}\n\treturn b, nil\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/config/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: PASS. Confirm `Parse` round-trips (`Template` output re-parses without error) by adding one spec asserting `Parse(mustTemplate(Default()))` succeeds.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace \u0026\u0026 git add internal/config/io.go internal/config/io_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(config): parse (strict), XDG path, and .bck-backed template write\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Two layers via the store + effective view\n\n### Task 4: Store-side project-entry discovery + trust filter\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/store/config.go`\n- Create: `internal/store/config_test.go`\n- Modify: `internal/store/store.go` (add `cfg *config.Config` field; load in `Open`; `Favorites()` accessor)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n`internal/store/config_test.go` (ginkgo, in the store suite): create a store in a temp repo, create a `kind:config` entry whose body sets `favorites` and a non-trusted key, then assert `s.EffectiveConfig()` merges the user file over it and drops the non-trusted key. Model setup on `internal/store/store_test.go` existing helpers (find the helper that opens a temp store — reuse it; do not invent one). Assert:\n```go\n// project entry contributes favorites (trusted by default) ...\nExpect(s.Favorites()).To(HaveKeyWithValue(\"todo\", \"aaaaaaaa\"))\n// ... but a key absent from trusted_keys is dropped with no error.\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 task test 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -30`\nExpected: FAIL — `s.Favorites` / `s.EffectiveConfig` undefined.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement discovery + trust filter**\n\n`internal/store/config.go`:\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"os\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/config\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox