f err := yaml.Unmarshal(b, \u0026doc); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, false, fmt.Errorf(\"config: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tv := readVersion(\u0026doc) // 0 when absent\n\tif v \u003e CurrentVersion {\n\t\treturn nil, false, fmt.Errorf(\"config version %d is newer than this kref (max %d); upgrade kref\", v, CurrentVersion)\n\t}\n\tif v == CurrentVersion {\n\t\treturn b, false, nil\n\t}\n\tstart := v\n\tif start \u003c 1 {\n\t\tstart = 1\n\t\tsetVersion(\u0026doc, 1)\n\t}\n\tfor i := start - 1; i \u003c len(migrations); i++ {\n\t\tif err := migrations[i](\u0026doc); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, false, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tsetVersion(\u0026doc, i+2)\n\t}\n\tsetVersion(\u0026doc, CurrentVersion)\n\tout, err = yaml.Marshal(\u0026doc)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, false, err\n\t}\n\treturn out, true, nil\n}\n```\n\nImplementer detail: `readVersion(*yaml.Node) int` and `setVersion(*yaml.Node, int)` walk the top-level mapping node's key/value pairs (a document node's `Content[0]` is the mapping). Add them in `migrate.go`. Keep `migrations` empty for v1 — the point is the machinery + newer-than-binary guard; the versionless-stamp path is what the test exercises.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cd /workspace \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/config/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace \u0026\u0026 git add internal/config/migrate.go internal/config/migrate_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(config): versioned migration chain with newer-than-binary guard\"\n```\n\n### Task 7: Auto-migrate the user file on load; `kref config migrate`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/store/config.go` (`loadUserConfig` migrates + rewrites when stale)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/config.go` (add `migrate` subcommand)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nIn `internal/store/config_test.go`, write a user file at an older/versionless shape into a temp `XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, open the store, and assert (a) the effective config